    <note>Cheng(1) Tang [124] During the Guangming period (880), his ancestor Qi [3098] followed Xizong into Sichuan, thereby moving from Wuchang jun (but really from Changan) to Meizhou, Meishan xian. Zhishao's [112] son, Zhicai's [113] and Zhiyuan's [114] nephew. The father or uncle of Dunzhi [125] (qv.) and Dunlin [126], who have the same generational names as his son Dunshu [3110]. Chao Gongsu, 52.7b-11b; XNYL, 30.1b; SHY:ZG, 43.99a-100a, 100a. CBD, 4, 3006.</note>
